sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1725224
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Lux A, Lux B, Lux C, Lux D, Lux E all under the control of the pBAD promoter (arabinose promoter)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cara Seggie

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1725212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LuxA and LuxB both with the ribosome binding site B0032. Together LuxA and LuxB can produce bioluminescence if decanal is present, which in the original lux operon is provided from the complex formed by LuxCDE.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Vibrio fischeri regulatory protein LuxR (luxR) gene
